Add a search box for searching inside the User settings ‚Äî Authentication logs. This is what the search box looks like:

![image](/uploads/a93db1bd75e3d24a472f30721e3c546a/image.png)

### Instructions

We already implemented a search box component in https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/292941. Adding the search box to this page is as simple as including a HAML partial and mounting the Search Vue application. 

```haml
= render "shared/search_settings"
```

The `search_settings` haml partial will display the search application only if the `search_settings_in_page` feature flag is enabled. Make sure to enable the feature flag locally to test your changes. 

```javascript
const mountSearchSettings = async () => {
  const el = document.querySelector('.js-search-settings-app');

  if (el) {
    const { default: initSearch } = await import(
      /* webpackChunkName: 'search_settings' */ '~/search_settings'
    );
    initSearch({ el, sectionSelector: '.row' });
  }
};

mountSearchSettings();
```

This JavaScript snippet will asynchronously load the search settings application only if the `search_settings` haml partial renders the application‚Äôs entry point element.

